mobile-frontend-home-button:
This appears in the mobile web menu, which appears when tapping the three stripes at the top corner.

This button takes the user to the home page of the wiki site.
{{Identical|Home}}

mobile-frontend-meta-data-issues:
Header of a collapsed section which, when tapped, displays some hidden content. The message is expected to generically state that the page could be better in some or several ways of unspecified nature, as reported by some or several cleanup/warning templates which this header hides. 

The button, when clicked, opens an overlay with heading {{msg-mw|mobile-frontend-meta-data-issues-header}}

This header is shown when the user clicks on a ambox template on a article.

mobile-frontend-random-button:
This appears in the mobile web menu, which appears when tapping the three stripes at the top corner.

This button takes the user to a random page.
{{Identical|Random}}

mobile-frontend-redirected-from:
Toast message informing the user that they were redirected from their original page. Parameters:
* $1 - the original page title from which the user was redirected

